{
  "quest.5663A6C559490A29.quest_desc": [
    "&6Right-Click&f the &bariel pearl&f on a &bzombie&f or &bhusk&f and it will be complete.",
  ],
  "quest.001579E45AFFB837.quest_desc": [
    "Looks can be deceiving! A &bCharged Snowball&r is more than just a frozen projectile.",
    "",
    "Created by &6Energizing&r a regular snowball, throwing it will summon a &elightning bolt&r wherever it lands or strikes a target. This makes it a fun tool for combat, redstone contraptions, or simply causing a little chaos.",
  ],
  "quest.07EF829BFBBB4009.quest_desc": [
    "The &6Energizing Orb&r is one of the most iconic machines in &bPowah&r, transforming ordinary items into powerful new materials using &eFE&r.",
    "",
    "To use it, place the required ingredients on the &6Energizing Orb&r and surround it with at least &aone Energizing Rod&r within a &b9×9&r area. The more rods you add, the higher their tier, the faster the energizing process becomes.",
    "",
    "Unlike most machines, the &6Orb itself doesn't consume power directly. Instead, each &aEnergizing Rod&r must be connected to an energy source, such as &bEnergy Cables&r or another block capable of supplying &eFE&r.",
    "",
    "Many advanced &6Powah&r components, including &bCharged Snowballs&r and higher-tier crafting materials, can only be created through the &6Energizing Orb&r.",
  ],
  "quest.001579E45AFFB837.quest_subtitle": "CHAAAAARGE!",
  "quest.292875386D7B9981.title": "&aUraninite",
  "quest.6E28C25469FF7738.quest_desc": [
    "Every great factory needs a reliable source of &eFE&r, and &6Powah&r offers several ways to keep the lights on.",
    "",
    "Choose the generator that best suits your needs:",
    "",
    "- &6Furnators&r consume burnable fuels like coal and charcoal to produce steady power.",
    "",
    "- &cMagmators&r harness the heat of lava, making them an excellent choice once you have a renewable lava supply.",
    "",
    "- &bThermo Generators&r generate energy from temperature differences and perform best when placed above extremely hot blocks.",
    "",
    "- &eSolar Panels&r passively generate power during the day, providing clean energy without consuming resources.",
  ],
  "quest.292875386D7B9981.quest_desc": [
    "&bUraninite &fis a ore you can get from &6mining&f. You can also get it from the &bMI Quarry&f. &bUraninite&f is a key part in powah and is used in alot of recipes and to power the &breactor.",
  ],
  "quest.00897CCAC72E82C5.quest_desc": [
    "Welcome to &6Powah&r!",
    "",
    "This mod is your gateway to reliable and scalable &eFE&r production, offering everything from simple generators to advanced reactors, wireless charging, and powerful automation tools.",
    "",
    "Throughout this questline, you'll learn how to generate, store, and distribute energy using &bPowah's&r unique machines and upgrades. Along the way, you'll unlock better power tiers and discover convenient utilities like &6Player Transmitters&r and &eBinding Cards&r.",
    "",
    "Whether you're powering a single machine or an entire factory, &6Powah&r has you covered.",
  ],
  "quest.06DED76B2F4AFD02.title": "Coolants",
  "quest.5663A6C559490A29.quest_subtitle": "Don't think your getting that zombie back",
  "quest.0897CCAC72E82C5.title": "&4Welcome to Powah!!!",
  "quest.0897CCAC72E82C5.quest_subtitle": "Need MOAR POWAH!, do you?",
  "task.7537E40C4FAB6D5C.title": "Welcome To Powah",
  "quest.6DED76B2F4AFD02.title": "Dry Ice",
  "quest.02476BE69FBC0681.title": "Reactors",
  "quest.3311C5BAAAEA0823.quest_desc": [
    "Cut the cords and take your &eFE&r anywhere with &6Powah's&r wireless power solutions!",
    "",
    "- &5Ender Cells&r create a shared energy network, allowing power to be stored in one place and accessed from anywhere—even across dimensions.",
    "",
    "- &bEnder Gates&r wirelessly send energy to compatible machines without the need for cables, making them perfect for clean and compact builds.",
    "",
    "- &dPlayer Transmitters&r keep &eyou&r powered by sending energy directly to your inventory. Pair them with a &6Binding Card&r or &5Dimensional Binding Card&r to charge your equipment wherever your adventures lead.",
  ],
  "quest.292875386D7B9981.quest_subtitle": "Might want to put some gloves on",
  "quest.3311C5BAAAEA0823.title": "Wireless Power",
  "quest.6E28C25469FF7738.title": "Power Generation",
  "quest.7EF829BFBBB4009.quest_desc": [
    "By placing Energizing rods around an Energizing Orb, then powering the rods, you can energize different materials inside the orb. This can range from single items to a combination of items.",
    "",
    "If you want to do this faster and quicker, you can energize in bulk! &bEnergizing&r can be sped up if you have enough &bpower&r. If you have the &bblocks&r rather then the &bingots&r, you can make the &benergized block 9x faster&r.",
  ],
  "quest.06DED76B2F4AFD02.quest_desc": [
    "Keeping your &cReactor&r cool is just as important as keeping it fueled!",
    "",
    "&6Reactors&r accept a variety of &bcoolants&r to improve efficiency and increase power output. While plain &9Water&r gets the job done, colder materials provide even better performance.",
    "",
    "You can use both &bfluids&r and &esolid blocks&r as coolants. Options range from &9Water&r and &bSnow&r all the way up to &3Packed Ice&r, &1Blue Ice&r, and &7Dry Ice&r for maximum cooling potential.",
  ],
  "quest.390323A83EB8009A.quest_desc": [
    "Generating power is only half the battle, you also need a way to &estore&r and &bmove&r it where it's needed.",
    "",
    "- &aEnergy Cables&r transfer &eFE&r between your generators, machines, and storage blocks.",
    "",
    "- &6Batteries&r act as portable energy buffers, storing power for later use or transport.",
    "",
    "- &9Energy Cells&r are larger stationary storage blocks, perfect for building up reserves and balancing your power network.",
  ],
  "quest.2476BE69FBC0681.quest_subtitle": "Might need hazmat for this structure",
  "quest.119752DA7C1B29B6.title": "Binding Cards",
  "quest.2476BE69FBC0681.title": "Reactors",
  "quest.2476BE69FBC0681.quest_desc": [
    "&bReactors&f are a very good source of&b power&f. They can generate thousands to hundreds of thousands of &bFE&f. They require &bredstone&f to slow the fuel consumption, &bcoal&f to boost the efficiency, &bice and water&f to cool the the reactor and of course &buraninite&f to power this &breactor&f.",
    "",
    "It take &b36 reactor blocks&f to make it, and they build themselves. Yah you heard me right, they will automatically build themselves if you have all &b36 blocks&b in your &6inventory &fand u &6place&f one of them the multiblock will form around it as a &b3x3x4&f.",
  ],
  "quest.119752DA7C1B29B6.quest_desc": [
    "&6Cards&r are used to &blink yourself&r to a &dPlayer Transmitter&r, allowing wireless energy to follow you wherever you go.",
    "",
    "* &fBlank Card&r ",
    "A simple crafting ingredient used to create the specialized cards below.",
    "",
    "* &bBinding Card&r ",
    "Bind this card to yourself and insert it into a &dPlayer Transmitter&r to wirelessly supply &eFE&r while you're in the &asame dimension&r.",
    "",
    "* &5Dimensional Binding Card&r ",
    "An upgraded Binding Card that keeps the connection active &bacross dimensions&r, letting the &dPlayer Transmitter&r provide power no matter where your adventures take you.",
    "",
    "Once paired with a &dPlayer Transmitter&r, these cards make it easy to keep powered equipment running without carrying bulky batteries or cables.",
  ],
  "quest.6DED76B2F4AFD02.quest_desc": [
    "&bDry ice &fis extremely rare to find underground, but you can make it if you have enough &bpower and ice.",
  ],
  "quest.07EF829BFBBB4009.title": "Energizing",
  "quest.6DED76B2F4AFD02.quest_subtitle": "A little cold to the touch",
  "quest.119752DA7C1B29B6.quest_subtitle": "Wireless Powah!",
  "quest.390323A83EB8009A.title": "Storage and Cables",
  "quest.02476BE69FBC0681.quest_desc": [
    "Ready to enter the &cendgame&r of &6Powah&r? It's time to harness the power of the &4Reactor&r!",
    "",
    "Unlike traditional generators, a &cReactor&r consumes &aUraninite&r to produce massive amounts of &eFE&r, making it one of the most powerful energy sources available. As long as it's supplied with fuel and kept cool, it can sustain even the most demanding factories.",
    "",
    "Build your reactor using &7Reactor Blocks&r and complete the multiblock structure before activating it. Upgrading to higher tiers will significantly increase both its efficiency and output.",
    "",
    "&6Tip:&r Pair your reactor with large &9Energy Cells&r or an &5Ender Cell&r network to buffer excess power and keep your entire base running smoothly.",
  ],
  "quest.0897CCAC72E82C5.quest_desc": [
    "&oPowah! is all about generating, storing, and transferring power",
    "&8*But not for Modern Industrialization",
  ],
}